Inspect or change cluster-wide policy

Usage:
  grainfs cluster config [command]

Available Commands:
  diff        Show only explicit overrides (vs code defaults)
  get         Print one cluster config value
  reset       Reset one or more keys to defaults
  set         Set one or more cluster config values (atomic single PATCH)
  show        Print all cluster config values (rev + effective + source)

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for config

Global Flags:
      --endpoint string    admin Unix socket path (required, e.g. ./tmp/admin.sock)
      --format string      Output format: text or json (status/peers/events; ignored elsewhere) (default "text")
      --log-level string   log level: debug, info, warn, error (default "info")

Use "grainfs cluster config [command] --help" for more information about a command.
